Not convinced.
leave Jennifer [animation="Instant Out"]
leave Maya [animation="Instant Out"]
leave Ricardo [animation="Instant Out"]
[background arg="res://Art/Backgrounds/mayas_room.png" fade="0.7"]
Maya enters her room and quietly closes the door.
She leans against it.
Taking a deep breath..
She opens her phone notifs and see people liking her posts about the art she's shared recently.
She smiles faintly.
Then her expression softens.
Maybe...
I should just tell them.
She imagines it.
Her parents.
The disappointment.
The questions.
The expectations.
Her smile fades.
She slowly shakes her head.
join Maya (neutral) left [animation="Instant In"]
Maya: Hindi pa... Nothing good would come out of it.
She places her phone near to her side.
Her laptop starts on again.
leave Maya [animation="Instant Out"]
[background arg="res://Mocks/Novel UI/image 3.png" fade="0.7"]
Jennifer scrolls through her own feed, half-watching TV.
A suggested post stops her thumb on an art account she almost swipes past.
Something about the name and the style feels familiar.
She taps it.
Maya's username sits quietly in the bio.
She stares at the screen for a long moment.
Blanky staring at all the newest posts.
One after the other.
Then locks it, she says nothing.
The house is unusually quiet.
The only sounds are the soft clinking of utensils against plates and the occasional hum of the ceiling fan.
Except the sounds of keyboard texts and videos playing.
By both Jennifer and Ricardo.
join Maya (neutral) left [animation="Instant In"]
Maya, Jennifer, and Ricardo sit around the dining table eating dinner.
Maya absentmindedly pushes the food around her plate.
She barely takes a bite.
